main event: On July 10, 1966, military personnel observed a round object in the sky over the Ryukyu Islands for 12 to 15 seconds.
interesting points: The object changed colors from bluish green to orange, The shape was described as round and larger than an aircraft, Multiple reliable military witnesses were involved, The object was reported to be at an estimated altitude of 210,000 feet, There was no radar detection of the object.
witness description: TSGT Self, TSGT Estep, AIC Connoroy, TSGT Kane, TSGT King - all highly reliable military personnel
